Source: Bulletin de Surveillance Sanitaire, Bureau de Ville Sanitaire, week 43 [in French, trans. Mod.TY and machine, edited]
http://www.hygiene-publique.gov.pf/IMG/pdf/bulletin_surv_pf_sem_43-2013.pdf


Epidemic syndromes due to Zika virus
------------------------------------
The cases are reported in the Society, Marquesas and Tuamotu Islands since week 41 [7-13 Oct 2013]. The number of cases is currently estimated at about 400, but the investigation is still ongoing. The islands affected are: Tahiti, Moorea, Raiatea, Tahaa, Bora Bora, Nuku Hiva and Arutua.

The signs are in initially a descending facial rash with itchy, urticarial or morbilliform lesions on limbs, accompanied inconsistently moderate fever, conjunctival hyperemia, arthralgia, myalgia, gastrointestinal disorders and distal edema. The duration of signs is [usually] 5-7 days, and the progression is self-limiting. [However, debilitating arthralgia may continue for many weeks or months. - Mod.TY]

--
