[Zika virus infections have appeared again in Pacific islands. There was a major outbreak of Zika virus infections on Yap and nearby islands of the Federated Republic of Micronesia in 2007. The vector mosquito of this flavivirus virus was not determined. It would be interesting to know if the mosquito vectors of Zika virus in the outbreak above have been determined.

ProMED thanks Dr. Mallet for calling this report to our attention.

A map showing the location of the island archipelagos in French Polynesia mentioned above can be accessed at http://www.worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/oceania/pf.htm and at http://healthmap.org/r/4tD1. - Mod.TY]
